A parking lock device for a vehicle having a right wheel (3RR) and a left wheel (3RL), comprising;

a right parking lock mechanism (6) which locks a rotation of the right wheel (3RR), the right parking lock mechanism (6) comprising a locking operation prevention mechanism (63c,63d) which mechanically prevents a locking operation of the right parking lock mechanism (6) when a wheel rotation speed of the right wheel (3RR) exceeds a predetermined parking lock prevention wheel rotation speed;

a left parking lock mechanism (6) which locks a rotation of the left wheel (3RL), the left parking lock mechanism (6) comprising a locking operation prevention mechanism (63c,63d) which mechanically prevents a locking operation of the left parking lock mechanism (6) when a wheel rotation speed of the left wheel (3RL) exceeds the predetermined parking lock prevention wheel rotation speed;

a rotation speed sensor (5R) which detects a wheel rotation speed of the right wheel (3RR);

a rotation speed sensor (5L) which detects a wheel rotation speed of the left wheel (3RL); and

a programmable controller (10) programmed to:
determine if a predetermined parking lock permitting condition is satisfied on the basis of the wheel rotation speed of the right wheel (3RR) and the wheel rotation speed of the left wheel (3RL) (S104, S202, S301, S402, S501); and
prevent the locking operation of both of the right parking lock mechanism (6) and the left parking lock mechanism (6) when the predetermined parking lock permitting condition is not satisfied,
wherein the controller (10) is further programmed to determine that the predetermined parking lock permitting condition is not satisfied when a difference between the wheel rotation speed of the right wheel (3RR) and the wheel rotation speed of the left wheel (3RL) is greater than a predetermined speed difference (S104, S202, S301, S402, S501).

