a rotation speed sensor (5R) which detects a wheel rotation speed of the right wheel (3RR);

a rotation speed sensor (5L) which detects a wheel rotation speed of the left wheel (3RL);

a running speed sensor (5a) which detects a vehicle running speed;

and

a programmable controller (10) programmed to:
determine if a predetermined parking lock permitting condition is satisfied on the basis of the wheel rotation speed of the right wheel (3RR) and the wheel rotation speed of the left wheel (3RL) (S104, S202, S301, S402, S501); and
prevent the locking operation of both of the right parking lock mechanism (6) and the left parking lock mechanism (6) when the predetermined parking lock permitting condition is not satisfied,
wherein the controller (10) is further programmed to determine that the predetermined parking lock permitting condition is not satisfied when one or both of a deviation between the wheel running speed of the right wheel (3RR) and the vehicle running speed and a deviation between the the wheel running speed of the left wheel (3RL) and the vehicle running speed is greater than a predetermined speed deviation (S202, S501).

